http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Congress-to-finalise-candidates-on-Jan.-18/article13985471.ece

A final list of candidates of the Congress for the elections to the zilla panchayat and taluk panchayat elections will be prepared on January 18 and will be submitted to the KPCC president and the Chief Minister on January 20, said B.J. Vijaya Kumar, president of the Mysuru District Congress Committee.A preliminary meeting of aspirant candidates and leaders of the district congress will be held on January 8 at 11 a.m. at the District Congress office here. Applications will be distributed at the taluk Congress offices for the aspirants from January 9. Mr. Kumar said that the party had decided not to give tickets to candidates having criminal background. The DCC also resolved not to give application forms to those who indulged in anti-party activities in the last few elections, he said. Youth and those who have been serving the party for many years would be given top priority in the selection of candidates to contest the panchayat elections, Mr. Vijayakumar said.Sitting members have to furnish the details of their performance in the last few years.